main event: A civilian observed an oval-shaped white fluorescent object at Randolph AFB, Texas, for 25 minutes.
interesting points: The object moved generally to the south with a slow disappearance,Observers were in a moving automobile,The sky was clear in the area of observation despite thunderstorms to the north,The sighting was concluded to be a probable balloon,Investigation showed no probable cause for the sighting.
witness description: civilian observers, employed at Kelly AFB and an aircraft electronic technician
